最早可追溯到[[美国内战|美国内战]]时期<ref>{{cite web |last=Lakin |first=Matt |url=http://www.knoxnews.com/news/local-news/history-shell-of-former-self |title=Deputies blow up Civil War ordnance found in Farragut |work=Knoxville News Sentinel |date=15 August 2008 |accessdate=5 March 2015 |archive-date=2015-07-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150715090746/http://www.knoxnews.com/news/local-news/history-shell-of-former-self |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.archaeology.org/9611/newsbriefs/civilwar.html |title=Live Civil War Ammo Found |work=Archaeology |volume=49 |issue=6 |date=November–December 1996 |accessdate=20 July 2013 |journal= |archive-date=2012-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121118181727/http://www.archaeology.org/9611/newsbriefs/civilwar.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/24441427|title=Civil War Cannonball Explodes and Kills Virginia Relic Collector|publisher=[[MSNBC|MSNBC]]|date=5 March 2008|accessdate=10 September 2010|archive-date=2012-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104060529/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/24441427|dead-url=no}}</ref> 的未爆炸弹药在当前或过去的作战地区或武装交火地区的存在在世界范围内仍是巨大隐患。 未爆炸弹药的一个主要问题是，随着时间流逝，弹药的爆炸和[[启动装置|启动装置]]逐渐腐化，从而导致其更容易被[[触发|触发]]，并且在处理时可能存在更大的危险性。无数案例显示，平民可能在无意中触碰已经存在很多年的未爆炸弹药，并造成致命伤害。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2595244/Seven-killed-Bangkok-workers-tried-dismantle-Second-World-War-bomb-blowtorch.html | location=London | work=Daily Mail | title=Seven die in Bangkok explosion after scrap metal dealers try to dismantle WWII bomb with a BLOWTORCH | first=Paul | last=Donnelley | date=2 April 2014 | accessdate=2015-05-14 | archive-date=2016-03-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304201351/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2595244/Seven-killed-Bangkok-workers-tried-dismantle-Second-World-War-bomb-blowtorch.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Gardner |first=Tom |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2534706/Ten-members-Pakistani-family-killed-artillery-shell-kept-house-explodes.html |title=Ten members of Pakistani family are killed when artillery shell they kept in home explodes |work=Daily Mail |date=6 January 2014 |accessdate=22 March 2014 |location=London |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304080926/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2534706/Ten-members-Pakistani-family-killed-artillery-shell-kept-house-explodes.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/regions/asia-pacific/vietnam/121203/unexploded-mortar-shell-kills-vietnamese-children |title=Unexploded mortar shell kills Vietnamese children |publisher=GlobalPost |date=3 December 2012 |accessdate=20 July 2013 |archive-date=2016-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160106083452/http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/regions/asia-pacific/vietnam/121203/unexploded-mortar-shell-kills-vietnamese-children |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.libyaherald.com/2012/11/18/two-people-killed-in-rubbish-dump-blast |title=Two officials killed by unexploded ordnance at rubbish dump in Hasawna |work=Libya Herald |date=18 November 2012 |accessdate=20 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121128135206/http://www.libyaherald.com/2012/11/18/two-people-killed-in-rubbish-dump-blast |archivedate=2012年11月28日 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-85505/Schoolboys-killed-unexploded-tank-shell.html |title=Schoolboys are killed by unexploded tank shell |work=Daily Mail |accessdate=20 July 2013 |location=London |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304082648/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-85505/Schoolboys-killed-unexploded-tank-shell.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2012/07/01/news/foreign/4-afghan-children-killed-by-unexploded-weaponry |title=4 Afghan children killed by unexploded weaponry |work=Pakistan Today |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=1 July 2012 |accessdate=20 July 2013 |archive-date=2012-06-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120630215914/http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2012/07/01/news/foreign/4-afghan-children-killed-by-unexploded-weaponry/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 他们相信该类武器是无害的，但事实上它却是致命且不稳定的爆炸物，一旦被触动就会爆发并对平民造成严重的甚至是致命性的伤害。<ref>{{cite news |last=Turvill |first=William |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2525684/Soldiers-anti-tank-missile-souvenir-exploded-blowing-friends-legs-off.html |title=Soldier's anti-tank missile 'souvenir' exploded blowing his friend's legs off |work=Daily Mail |date=18 December 2013 |accessdate=22 March 2014 |location=London |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304091718/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2525684/Soldiers-anti-tank-missile-souvenir-exploded-blowing-friends-legs-off.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>因此，应当形成全球共识的是，未受过专业训练的人不应该接触或处置未爆炸弹药。此外，在发现未爆炸弹药后，应当告知当地警局未爆炸弹药的具体位置，由[[爆炸物处理专员|爆炸物处理专员]]对其进行拆除或确保其安全。

即使爆炸物处理专员拥有专业的知识、技术和装备，由于未爆炸炮弹的内在危险，他们仍然很容易遭受不幸。2010年六月，[[德国哥廷根|德国哥廷根]]建筑工人在7米的地下发现了[[二战|二战]]时期被掩埋的盟军炮弹，炮弹重达500公斤。 德国爆炸物处理专员接到通知后接管了这一地区并通知附近居民进行了疏散。正在爆炸物处理专员准备拆除炸弹时，炮弹突然[[爆炸|爆炸]]，3名爆炸物处理专员遇难，另有6人重伤。据了解，遇难和受伤的爆炸物处理专员已有超过20年排爆经验，并成功排除了600到700个未爆炸弹药的潜在危险。 此次爆炸的未爆炸弹药被列入极高危险性一类，由于它安装了延迟爆炸的化学引信，并内置[[反排装置|反排装置]]，在被埋地下超过65年后其状态已变得极为不稳定。<ref>{{cite web |author=International |url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/0,1518,698245,00.html |title=Routine Disposal Goes Wrong: Three Killed in Explosion of World War II Bomb in Germany |work=Der Spiegel |date=2 June 2010 |accessdate=20 July 2013 |archive-date=2012-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120129160812/http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/0,1518,698245,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/10212890.stm | publisher=BBC News | title=WWII bomb kills three in Germany | date=2 June 2010 | accessdate=2015-05-14 | archive-date=2020-02-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229171802/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/10212890 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/germany/7795709/Three-dead-as-Second-World-War-bomb-explodes-in-Germany.html|title=Three dead as Second World War bomb explodes in Germany|work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]|date=2 June 2010|accessdate=10 September 2010|location=London|archive-date=2018-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622175010/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/germany/7795709/Three-dead-as-Second-World-War-bomb-explodes-in-Germany.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailyexpress.co.uk/posts/view/178648/Bomb-kills-German-explosive-experts/ |title=Bomb kills German explosive experts |work=Daily Express |date=2 June 2010 |accessdate=20 July 2013 |archive-date=2010-06-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100605023829/http://www.dailyexpress.co.uk/posts/view/178648/Bomb-kills-German-explosive-experts |dead-url=no }}</ref> 同样，2013年1月，二战时期空投的一颗炸弹在[[奥伊斯基|奥伊斯基]]一建筑物内爆炸，导致一名[[挖掘机|挖掘机]]操作员死亡，8人受伤，并造成大面积财产损失。<ref>{{cite news |last=Malm |first=Sara |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2533304/German-construction-worker-killed-unexploded-World-War-Two-bomb-dug-trench-Digger-driver-dies-instantly-explosion-near-Bonn.html |title=World War II bomb detonated on industrial site in Euskirchen, Germany, killing one |work=Daily Mail |date=3 January 2014 |accessdate=22 March 2014 |location=London |archive-date=2015-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804162123/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2533304/German-construction-worker-killed-unexploded-World-War-Two-bomb-dug-trench-Digger-driver-dies-instantly-explosion-near-Bonn.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 2013年11月，4名[[美国海军|美国海军]]亦在清除[[彭德尔顿|彭德尔顿]]营一个靶场的未爆炸弹药时遇难。<ref>{{cite news |last=Thomas |first=Emma |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2507059/Four-marines-killed-accident-US-Camp-Pendleton-clearing-explosives-firing-range.html |title=Four marines killed in accident at US Camp Pendleton were clearing explosives from firing range |work=Daily Mail |date=14 November 2013 |accessdate=22 March 2014 |location=London |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304075934/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2507059/Four-marines-killed-accident-US-Camp-Pendleton-clearing-explosives-firing-range.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

